A rugby league player has told how a heavy tackle left him in pain - only to be diagnosed with a broken neck three days later.

Wests Tigers player Keith Lulia walked off the field after picking up what he thought was a minor injury during a game against the North Queensland earlier this month - but now may never play again.

The life changing moment occurred when Lulia was going in to make a cover tackle on Kane Linnett on the night the Tigers experienced a 64-6 annihilation by the Cowboys in Townsville.

Aware of how lucky he is, the utility back is remaining positive about the prospect of ever playing again after his neck broke from the pressure of the top of his head colliding with Linnet’s hip.

