Lulia asked for further tests to be done after he failed the cog test twice.

'So he sent me for a scan and it showed there was a break, a clean break,' he said.

He said he knows how blessed he is to still have movement in his neck.

'I am just lucky that so far there is no nerve damage and hopeful it heals up 100 per cent,' he said.

'It is just the pain I have to deal with at the moment.'

